Turksâ€™ Spending on Technology Products Rises 19.4%, GfK Reports

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-03-07T07:21:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/turks-spending-on-technology-products-rises-19-4-gfk-reports.html
Turks spent 17.5 billion liras ($11
billion) on technology products last year, 19.4 percent more
than in 2009, a survey by research company GfK showed.  Spending on telecommunications products, including
smartphones, grew 41.8 percent, to 4.2 billion liras, GfK said
in an e-mailed statement yesterday. Home-appliance spending grew
by 10.2 percent, to 5.4 billion liras, and that on consumer
electronics, including LCDs and LED TVs, by 21.1 percent, to 2.5
billion liras, according to the survey.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
